input {
  border: 1px solid green;
  width: 100%;
  padding: 5px;
}
label {
  font-weight: bold;
  color: green;
}

The style will also apply to the button

We can target the input elements by their type using the following syntax:

input[type='text'] {
  border: 1px solid green;
  width: 100%;
  padding: 5px;
} 

This will only apply the style to <input type="text"> elements.

We can also style the text inside the text fields, just like any other text.

input[type='text'], input[type='email'] {
  border:1px solid green;
  width:100%;
  padding: 5px;
  color: green;
  font-weight: bold;
} 


Similarly, we can apply a style to our button:

input[type='button'] {
  background-color: green;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 20px;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  font-weight: bold;
  color: white;
} 
We used border:none to remove the default border from the button.
we can use the :hover pseudo selector to style the button, when it is hovered:

input[type='button']:hover {
  background-color: gray;
} 